training_sentences.sentence: next level roads congress of counties surveygovernor eric holcomb launched indianas next level roads plan this week
the 47 billion 5year plan will upgrade thousands of miles of hoosier highways and roads and theres more to come thanks to the 20year plan passed during our latest legislative session

you can learn more about the announcement and see exactly which roads are on the list belowin addition i want to personally ask you to participate in a short survey we created to help us plan for this years congress of counties
historically held in oddnumbered years congress of counties is a twoday training held to equip our top activists volunteers and leaders with the tools and technology they need to succeed

to make this years event the best yet we need to hear from you please take a few moments to share your thoughts on where congress of counties should be held and what should be included in the programming so we can better prepare for an enjoyable and informative weekend this falldont forget governor holcombs sporting clay shoot with first lady janet holcomb colts kicker adam vinatieri taking place on tuesday
for more information contact zach willis at zachwillisholcombforindianacom

this event benefits team holcomb the joint fundraising committee for the indiana republican party and eric holcomb for indiana kylegovernor holcombs week that wasas mentioned above governor holcomb put tires to pavement this week as he made stops in indianapolis lafayette terre haute evansville and sellerburg with extra stops in covington and bruceville to unveil indianas next level roads plan
the first 5 years of our 20year infrastructure plan will invest 47 billion on indianas roads and bridges
a total of 122 lane miles will be added 9628 lane miles will be resurfaced and 1295 bridges will be rehabbed or replaced

in addition to scheduled work on state roads theplan calls for an additional 342 million annually to be invested in local city county and town infrastructurethis longterm sustainable datadriven infrastructure plan is fully funded and will maintain indianas position as the crossroads of america for generations to comefind out which projects are coming to your county by checking out the full next level roads plan here

click here to apply health care updatesenate majority leader mitch mcconnell unveiled the latest version of the better care reconciliation act on thursday
as senator mcconnell and others said the initial bill was a discussion draft and this revamped legislation includes some important provisions that have been included based on those discussions

these additions includemore help to cover outofpocket costs an additional 70 billion is dedicated to encouraging statebased reforms which could include help with driving down premiums through costsharing health savings accounts hsa and other innovative ideas to help pay for health care costs

this is in addition to the 112 billion in funding already in the original billhealth savings accounts to pay for premiums in order to ensure that more people have financial support to pay for health care costs a provision has been included in the bill that would for the first time allow people to use their hsas to pay for their premiums

kaine for virginiawhen i was running for president one of the things i said so often is that we need more love and kindness in this country
these are the values that have always motivated me and theyre a big part of why i chose tim kaine as my running mate

if you mention tim to anyone who knows him whether its a member of his church congregation who sang with him in the choir or a republican senator who works with him across the aisle youre likely to hear the same thing tim is a guy who believes in love and kindness
im proud to call tim and anne my friends and im doing all i can to support tim in his reelection campaign
will you join me
heres the thing losing the election was hard for all of us
its also hard to keep mustering the energy to continue fighting day after day for the america we still believe in
but what would be hardest of all is giving uptim is someone who never gives up
when we lost in november he didnt even take a vacation he went right back to work for virginians in the senate
for tim there was no rest for the weary

guided by his love of this country and his care for the people he serves he knew he had to continue to fight for whats right for virginians and all americans inch by inch tooth and nail no matter the obstacle
and now more than ever thats what we need in the senate
so today im asking you to help make sure we keep him thereplease join me in supporting tims campaign by pitching in 10 or whatever you can right now

tim and i are both guided by faith and during the campaign we always reminded one another of this creed do all the good you can for all the people you can in all the ways you can as long as ever you canlets make sure tim can keep doing good for virginia families in the senate
